    {
        "user": "UA14TGLTC",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1779155475.876619",
        "edited": {
            "user": "UA14TGLTC",
            "ts": "1779155510.000000"
        },
        "client_msg_id": "8935878e-c041-4f41-8f15-3292a28e20d9",
        "text": "I know some real Musk fans: people who've worked with him and like it.  However, he is the kind of person who does not know the limits of his competency, so it's hard to know whether a given comment is worth paying attention to.  And Rogan as interviewer is the not the least bit critical.  So that should help explain why even a minute long quote like this would not be deemed worthy of attention.\n\nOn to the substance though: I'm really interested in the idea of AI used for bespoke interfaces.  And one thing I've learned is that you want a means by which a one-off answer\/process that the AI thought hard to give becomes automated. codified. and standardized.  Not for efficiency sake, but for predictability.  You want to know that the view is a \"simple,\" reproducible function of the underlying data.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "gae6d55db9d1",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/3ae6d55db9d15b79bc683a8031fc2588.jpg?s=72&d=https%3A%2F%2Fa.slack-edge.com%2Fdf10d%2Fimg%2Favatars%2Fava_0009-72.png",
            "first_name": "",
            "real_name": "William Taysom",
            "display_name": "wtaysom",
            "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
            "name": "wtaysom",
            "is_restricted": false,
            "is_ultra_restricted": false
        },
        "thread_ts": "1779126438.094529",
        "parent_user_id": "UJFN50C00",
        "blocks": [
            {
                "type": "rich_text",
                "block_id": "ZOL5l",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "I know some real Musk fans: people who've worked with him and like it.  However, he is the kind of person who does not know the limits of his competency, so it's hard to know whether a given comment is worth paying attention to.  And Rogan as interviewer is the not the least bit critical.  So that should help explain why even a minute long quote like this would not be deemed worthy of attention.\n\nOn to the substance though: I'm really interested in the idea of AI used for bespoke interfaces.  And one thing I've learned is that you want a means by which a one-off answer\/process that the AI thought hard to give becomes automated. codified. and standardized.  Not for efficiency sake, but for predictability.  You want to know that the view is a \"simple,\" reproducible function of the underlying data."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
