    {
        "user": "UJBAJNFLK",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1779170263.768409",
        "client_msg_id": "b4a806f1-8436-4166-b525-fe5cef32b990",
        "text": "<@UD4Q9LT52>\n&gt; If we hit post-scarcity\nWe won't. That's the other problem with people like Elon Musk (in addition to being a bad person): hubris. If you listen to anyone who has made a serious effort to understand stocks and flows of resources in our universe, you will find out that this dream of post-scarcity will never come true, unless there are very serious and resource-relevant holes in our understanding of physics.\nWell, there is one exception: a drastic reduction of the human population of this planet. The survivors can enjoy post-scarcity for a while. At a poverty level, but still.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "e169f54bbaf8",
